      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index comparison against Heck et al. in vitro loop",
      "description": "Predicted RH values across the five flow-speed operating points were benchmarked against the Heck et al. (2017) in vitro hemolysis loop dataset. The Heck dataset is widely cited, fully documented, and uses the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, closed-loop mock circulation, and identical NIH hemolysis power-law (C=3.62e-7, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785). Agreement across all five points was within 12% on RH, well under the 25% tolerance. The comparator is well-characterized and has been used in multiple regulatory submissions, supporting the declared acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-pressure-rise",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
